cc:Work.dc:title: Lindworm Snake
cc:Work.dc:description: Lindworms, also called Lindorms or Lindorm Snakes, were monsters in the ancient world that may have lived as late as the thirteenth century. Swifter than it looks, one of these beasts was capable of overtaking a man on a galloping horse. They are believed to be extinct now. The precise coloring of this illustration is somewhat conjectural.
